---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import TopBar from '../../components/TopBar.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Green Roof Plants – LiveRoof Products">
  <TopBar />
  <Header />

  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Plants"
    title="RoofTop Proven™"
    highlight="Green Roof Plants"
    subtitle="Dozens of exclusive varieties bred and tested specifically for rooftop performance — selected for drought tolerance, vigor, and beauty in your local climate."
    breadcrumbs={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Products', href: '/products' },
      { label: 'Plants' },
    ]}
  />

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="py-14 md:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Expert Selection</span>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-[2.2rem] leading-[1.18] text-dark mb-5">Plants Are Not One-Size-Fits-All</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Green roof plants are not one-size-fits-all, and the individual requirements of each green roof
            design must be taken into consideration. Your LiveRoof Licensed Grower is an experienced horticultural
            professional who will examine the particular needs of your project and assist in selection of the
            best plants to bring your design to life.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Some green roof companies tout having a horticulturist on staff — but we have <strong class="text-green font-semibold">dozens,
            in different climates</strong>, most with decades of experience growing plants for and in that local environment.
          </p>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Find Your Local LiveRoof Rep</a>
        </div>
        <div class="photo-placeholder rounded-xl aspect-[4/3]">
          <svg width="48" height="48" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3" />
            <circle cx="8.5" cy="8.5" r="1.5" />
            <path d="m6 21 5.5-7 3.5 4 2.5-3L21 21" />
          </svg>
          <span>Sedum Varieties</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Climate, Development, Maintenance -->
  <section class="py-14 md:py-24 bg-mid">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-[0_2px_20px_rgba(35,31,32,0.06)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-green-light flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="#00B25A" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12 2C6.5 2 2 6.5 2 12s4.5 10 10 10 10-4.5 10-10S17.5 2 12 2z" />
              <path d="M2 12h20M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-[1.25rem] text-dark mb-3">Climate Matters</h3>
          <p class="text-[0.9rem] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            On the roof, attention to local conditions is even more critical. In Toronto, plants must handle
            rapid temperature changes and long winters. In Texas, they must endure prolonged heat, low precipitation,
            and heavy humidity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-[0_2px_20px_rgba(35,31,32,0.06)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-blue-light flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="#0092CF" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M7 20l4-16m2 16l4-16M6 9h14M4 15h14" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-[1.25rem] text-dark mb-3">Plant Development</h3>
          <p class="text-[0.9rem] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            We strive to be the industry leader in developing plants specifically suited to harsh green roof
            conditions. With dozens of introductions, our RoofTop Proven™ line provides vigorous, hardy, and
            consistent varieties.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-[0_2px_20px_rgba(35,31,32,0.06)]">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-green-light flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="#00B25A" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-[1.25rem] text-dark mb-3">Lower Maintenance</h3>
          <p class="text-[0.9rem] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            We focus on longevity — plants that are hardy with strong growth habits that deter weeds through
            dense soil coverage. Using lean, preventative maintenance practices, owners can expect beautiful,
            healthy systems that stand the test of time.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Important Note -->
      <div class="mt-12 bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-green">
        <p class="text-[0.92rem] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-dark">Important:</strong> There is no such thing as a maintenance-free green roof.
          Plants are living things and have basic requirements for survival. Neglected green roofs, regardless of
          plant selection, location and design, are more susceptible to stress from drought, weed encroachment,
          wind scour, pests and disease.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Best Plants & Biodiversity -->
  <section class="py-14 md:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Plant Selection</span>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-[2rem] text-dark mb-4">Best Plants for Green Roofs</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
            In the Lite and Standard systems, we recommend plants with extreme drought resistance through
            means other than the root system — succulent, water-holding plants like <strong class="text-green font-semibold">Sedums,
            Alliums, Sempervivums, and Delospermas</strong>.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The best LiveRoof plants store water and have "Crassulacean Acid Metabolism" (CAM). CAM plants
            exchange gases at night when it is cooler — making them up to <strong class="text-green font-semibold">ten times more
            efficient with water</strong> than non-CAM plants.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            In the Deep and Maxx systems with irrigation, a much broader plant palette is possible — including
            hundreds of native forbs, sedges, grasses, and edible plants.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <span class="tag">Biodiversity</span>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-[2rem] text-dark mb-4">Biodiverse Green Roofs</h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Green roofs with 6" or greater soil depth can support a broad array of plants, and biodiversity
            in plant and animal communities becomes very feasible.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Every biodiverse green roof requires a built-in irrigation system. Even drought-resistant native
            plants can only extract so much water from 6–8 inches of soil — on a rooftop, they can't send roots
            down several feet like they would in nature.
          </p>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Biodiverse LiveRoofs range from gardenlike (designed patterns) to meadowlike (random) and are
            typically very beautiful and seasonally dynamic. We've provided hundreds of biodiverse plantings —
            and we love them all.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Edible Plants -->
  <section class="py-10 md:py-16 bg-dark">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <span class="tag">Rooftop Gardening</span>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-[2rem] text-white mb-4">Grow Vegetables on Your Roof</h2>
      <p class="text-white/60 max-w-[560px] mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Numerous vegetables, herbs, and select fruits may be grown on intensive green roofs with the Maxx module.
        A blend of organic soil and traditional green roof media yields the best results.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBanner />
  <Footer />
</Layout>
